SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04634535
Version: 1

HPSBGN03316 rev.1 - HP Support Solution Framework on Windows, Remote
Execution of Code, Disclosure of Information

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2015-04-10
Last Updated: 2015-04-10

Potential Security Impact: Remote execution of code, disclosure of
information

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been discovered with the HP Support
Solution Framework used from HP support web pages to identify products, find
solutions and help with HP update downloads. The vulnerability could be
exploited to allow an unauthorized download of software on the customer
machine.

References:

CVE-2015-2114
SSRT102005

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
Note: All versions of HP Support Solution Framework prior to 11.51.0049
running on all versions of Windows are vulnerable.

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2015-2114    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:N)       5.8
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks Thomas Forbes for reporting this issue to
security-alert@...com.

RESOLUTION

HP has provided the following update and mitigation information to resolve
the vulnerability in HP Support Solution Framework.

Update HP Support Solution Framework to version 11.51.0049 by visiting
http://support.hp.com/ and clicking on "Identify Now".
Remove older versions of HP Support Solution Framework via the Program
management Control Panel.

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 10 April 2015 Initial release

